headline: JPM, BAC, and MS: How U.S. Bank Stocks Line Up in the Trump Era
summary: The banking world feels like a high-stakes poker game. The chips are flying, the players are tense, and the dealer (i.e., the global economy) keeps throwing wild cards. Tariffs are spiking, markets are swinging, and whispers of a recession are growing louder. Yet, JPMorgan Chase (JPM), Bank of America (BAC), and Morgan Stanley (MS) are still at the table, brushing off market anxiety like seasoned risk takers.
